column1: Before 1 January 2023, will negotiations on a China-Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) free trade agreement be completed?

column6: because China does not understand culture
3 months to go and bumping up off the back of positive talks between the parties, a quote from the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs (1);

I’m having trouble finding the articles I originally looked at, but I think China recently met with some of the GCC countries at the UN to discuss their continued plans about working towards a free trade agreement. Here is something I found right now, but it’s different than the stuff I was looking at a week or two ago: https://global.chinadaily.com.cn/a/202209/21/WS632afde3a310fd2b29e7900f.html
